article.headline: Saint Joseph's 68, Massachusetts 64
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- Ahmad Nivins had 21 points and 12 rebounds as St. Joseph's came from behind to beat Massachusetts 68-64 on Sunday. Tasheed Carr added 14 points, six rebounds and five assists for St. Joseph's (14-8, 7-1 Atlantic 10 Conference), which avoided the upset bug that has troubled the rest of the conference top teams. Massachusetts led 37-34 at halftime and led by eight early in the second half. An Anthony Gurley 3-pointer gave the Minutemen a 53-48 lead with 7:26 remaining. But the Massachusetts (8-13, 3-5 A-10 A-10) offense went cold from there as St. Joseph's went on a 15-3 run to pull ahead after the Minutemen couldn't respond. Gurley and Ricky Harris each had 18 for the Minutemen, while Tony Gaffney added eight points and 13 rebounds.
